   "source": [
    "### Define new colormap with matplotlib"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Here, give an example of create cmap using [LinearSegementedColormap](https://matplotlib.org/3.3.2/api/_as_gen/matplotlib.colors.LinearSegmentedColormap.html):"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from matplotlib.colors import LinearSegmentedColormap\n",
    "\n",
    "# give a list of color (color gradient)\n",
    "gradient = ['#FFFFFF','#FFDFAF','#FF7555','#FF2600','#F70000']\n",
    "\n",
    "my_cmap = LinearSegmentedColormap.from_list('interaction', gradient)\n",
    "my_cmap.set_bad(\"white\")\n",
    "my_cmap.set_under(\"white\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1133.86x626.457 with 7 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 9,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "frame = XAxis() + \\\n",
    "    Cool(cool_path, cmap=my_cmap)\n",
    "\n",
    "frame.plot(\"chr9:4000000-6000000\")"
   ]
  }
